@startuml
title Figure 8. DocuTracker System Architecture

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #666666
  FontColor #222222
}
skinparam package {
  BorderColor #888888
  FontColor #222222
}
skinparam database {
  BorderColor #A67C00
  BackgroundColor #FFF3CD
}
skinparam cloud {
  BorderColor #7A5FA3
  BackgroundColor #EFE7FA
}

left to right direction

package "Actors" #F8F9FA {
  actor Employee
  actor Reviewer
  actor Administrator
}

package "Client Layer (Flutter)" #EAF2FF {
  [DocuTracker App UI\n- Dashboard / Documents / Admin\n- Provider state management\n- Repository API client] as FlutterApp
}

package "Server Layer (Node.js + Express)" #EDF8EA {
  [DocuTracker API\n/api/docutracker routes] as Api
  [Workflow Engine\n- transitions\n- assignee resolution\n- permission checks] as Workflow
  [Escalation Worker\n- deadline scan\n- overdue escalation] as Worker
}

package "Data & Integration" #F6F1FA {
  database "PostgreSQL\nDocuTracker + HRMS tables" as Postgres
  rectangle "Attachment Storage\nuploads/docutracker-attachments" as Storage #FDECEC
  cloud "HRMS Source Modules\nLD / DTR / RSP (optional links)" as Sources
}

Employee --> FlutterApp : create / submit
Reviewer --> FlutterApp : review / approve
Administrator --> FlutterApp : configure

FlutterApp --> Api : REST + JWT
Api --> Workflow : route requests
Worker --> Workflow : escalate events

Workflow --> Postgres : read/write data
Workflow --> Storage : store / fetch files
Workflow --> Sources : source-linked docs (optional)

@enduml

